 <div class="review-header">
  <div class="review-meta">
   <h5>
    <span class="customerReviewTitle">Good but could be great :)</span>
    <div class='rating' role='img' tabindex='-1' aria-label='3 stars'><div><span class="rating-star">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star ghost">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star ghost">&nbsp;</span></div></div>

   </h5>
   <span class="user-info">by
    <a href='https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewUsersUserReviews?userProfileId=31644462' class="reviewer">Fitztacular</a>
     -
     Version
     2.8.0
    
    -
    Sep 15, 2017
   </span>
  </div>
  <div class="review-see-all">
   <a href='https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewUsersUserReviews?userProfileId=31644462' class="see-all">
   All Reviews by This User
   </a>
  </div>
 </div>
 <p class="content" data-text-truncate-lines="6">
  Like this chat app a lot. Saves me a lot of time with its built-in features as well as the available integrations. Also a big fan of the styling, makes work chat less boring!<br/><br/>However, noticed with recent update that the &quot;Slack Helper&quot; processes are chugging CPU time, so much so that the fans on my top-spec Macbook Pro run on medium to high. Didn‚Äôt have this issue before so I‚Äôm sure this is an optimization they just need to make.<br/><br/>One thing I would LOVE to see is the ability to ‚Äúsleep‚Äù a group, so that it didn‚Äôt have to be always running in the background. For someone like me, who uses Slack for 9 different groups, having each of those chats actively run leads to each spinning up a Slack Helper process that consumes a fair amount of CPU. Would love to be able to ‚Äúsleep‚Äù less important chats e.g. disable background updates for those groups until I explicitly ‚Äúun-sleep‚Äù it. This would primarily be used for chats of lower priority than others.
 </p>
 
 
  <div class="developer-response">
    <span class="developer-info">
        <span class="developer-response-title">Developer Response</span>
        -
        Oct 11, 2017
    </span>
      <p><span></span></p>
   <span class="developer-response-body">
        <p class="content" data-text-truncate-lines="2">
            Interesting idea about &quot;sleeping&quot; a workspace! You've given us some great food for thought here‚Äî thanks for sharing this with us!
        </p>
    </span>
   </div>
 
 
