 <p class="content" data-text-truncate-lines="6">
  Like this chat app a lot. Saves me a lot of time with its built-in features as well as the available integrations. Also a big fan of the styling, makes work chat less boring!<br/><br/>However, noticed with recent update that the &quot;Slack Helper&quot; processes are chugging CPU time, so much so that the fans on my top-spec Macbook Pro run on medium to high. Didn‚Äôt have this issue before so I‚Äôm sure this is an optimization they just need to make.<br/><br/>One thing I would LOVE to see is the ability to ‚Äúsleep‚Äù a group, so that it didn‚Äôt have to be always running in the background. For someone like me, who uses Slack for 9 different groups, having each of those chats actively run leads to each spinning up a Slack Helper process that consumes a fair amount of CPU. Would love to be able to ‚Äúsleep‚Äù less important chats e.g. disable background updates for those groups until I explicitly ‚Äúun-sleep‚Äù it. This would primarily be used for chats of lower priority than others.
 </p>
 
 
