   <h5>
    <span class="customerReviewTitle">Horrible on mac</span>
    <div class='rating' role='img' tabindex='-1' aria-label='2 stars'><div><span class="rating-star">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star ghost">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star ghost">&nbsp;</span><span class="rating-star ghost">&nbsp;</span></div></div>

   </h5>
   <span class="user-info">by
    <a href='https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewUsersUserReviews?userProfileId=42267990' class="reviewer">jenniferkvelez</a>
     -
     Version
     2.8.1
    
    -
    Oct 11, 2017
   </span>
  </div>
  <div class="review-see-all">
   <a href='https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewUsersUserReviews?userProfileId=42267990' class="see-all">
   All Reviews by This User
   </a>
  </div>
 </div>
 <p class="content" data-text-truncate-lines="6">
  This app has so much potential. I rely on it for work, yet it never seems to work for me as it should. I depend on my mac for gestures. I love swiping between full screen pages because that‚Äôs what a mac can do! That‚Äôs what a mac supports! You never need to compromise on screen real estate for any of your apps. And Slack for me needs to be full screen, so I can follow long threads at work, so I can see large images, so I lose none of it! When I open a document while in fullscreen, and then attempt to exit the document and return to my conversation or channel, it always manages to turn black. I am unable to close the application, minimize it, nothing. I have to force quit the app every time. Please please please fix this.
 </p>
 
 
  <div class="developer-response">
    <span class="developer-info">
        <span class="developer-response-title">Developer Response</span>
        -
        Oct 24, 2017
    </span>
      <p><span></span></p>
   <span class="developer-response-body">
        <p class="content" data-text-truncate-lines="2">
            We're so sorry about this negative experience, Jennifer. We are also working to resolve this bug with opening documents in fullscreen where you're left with a black screen afterwards. We hope to have it fixed soon. Thanks for bearing with us.
        </p>
    </span>
   </div>
 
 
